movie /ˈmuːvɪ/

(movies) 

1. N-COUNT A movie is a series of moving pictures that have been recorded so that they can be shown in a theatre or on television. A movie tells a story, or shows a real situation. 电影 

例： In the first movie Tony Curtis ever made he played a grocery clerk. 在托尼·柯蒂斯制作的第一部影片中，他出演一名杂货店店员。 

2. N-PLURAL You can talk about the movies when you are talking about seeing a movie in a movie theatre. 看电影 [美国英语]

</div>

